byline.contributor: Salman Masood reported from Islamabad, and Niki Kitsantonis from Athens.
byline.original: By SALMAN MASOOD and NIKI KITSANTONIS

abstract: Pakistan sends 30 migrants who arrived in Islamabad by plane back to Europe; officials quarrel over protocol on handling of Pakistani refugees, who are arriving with flow of Middle Eastern migrants, but fled primarily for economic reasons and are being referred to as 'unverfiied deportees.'
lead_paragraph: The asylum seekers were not allowed to disembark from a chartered plane at an Islamabad airport, officials said, reflecting growing frustration with European countries.

headline.main: Pakistan Sends 30 Migrants Back to Europe
headline.print_headline: 30 Migrants Are Returned to Europe by Pakistan
